### RULE 3: Security Misconfiguration — CWE-16

**BAD — Permissive defaults:**
```
// CORS: allow everything
cors({ origin: "*" })
Access-Control-Allow-Origin: *
Access-Control-Allow-Credentials: true   // NEVER combine with wildcard origin

// CSP: disabled or too permissive
Content-Security-Policy: default-src *
Content-Security-Policy: script-src 'unsafe-inline' 'unsafe-eval'

// Missing security headers entirely
// No HSTS, no X-Content-Type-Options, no X-Frame-Options

// Debug mode in production
app.config["DEBUG"] = True
app.run(debug=True)

// TLS: weak configuration
ssl_context.minimum_version = TLSv1_0          // Should be TLSv1_2+
ssl_context.set_ciphers("ALL")                 // Includes weak ciphers
```

**GOOD — Restrictive defaults:**
```
cors({ origin: ["https://app.example.com"], credentials: true })

headers = {
    "Content-Security-Policy": "default-src 'self'; script-src 'self'",
    "Strict-Transport-Security": "max-age=31536000; includeSubDomains",
    "X-Content-Type-Options": "nosniff",
    "X-Frame-Options": "DENY",
    "Referrer-Policy": "strict-origin-when-cross-origin"
}

app.config["DEBUG"] = environment.get("DEBUG", False)   // Off by default
```

